.\" Man page for rucho(1)
.TH RUCHO 1 "2026-02-16" "rucho 1.4.4" "Rucho Manual"
.SH NAME
rucho \- HTTP echo server and request inspector
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rucho
.I command
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rucho
is a fast, lightweight HTTP echo server built with Rust and Axum.
It echoes back request details (headers, body, method, URL, query parameters)
as JSON, making it useful for testing and debugging HTTP clients, proxies,
load balancers, and API integrations.
.PP
Features include HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2 support, HTTPS via Rustls, TCP and UDP
echo listeners, response compression, connection keep-alive tuning, chaos
engineering mode, request timing, and OpenAPI/Swagger documentation.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B start
Start the rucho server. Writes a PID file and begins listening on the
configured addresses.
.TP
.B stop
Stop a running rucho server by sending a termination signal to the
process identified in the PID file.
.TP
.B status
Check whether the rucho server is currently running.
.TP
.B version
Display the rucho version.
.SH ENDPOINTS
.TS
l l.
Path	Description
_
/	Welcome message
/get	Echo GET request details
/post	Echo POST request with body
/put	Echo PUT request with body
/patch	Echo PATCH request with body
/delete	Echo DELETE request details
/options	Return allowed methods
/anything	Echo any request method
/anything/*path	Echo any request with subpath
/status/:code	Return specified HTTP status code
/delay/:n	Delay response by n seconds (max 300)
/redirect/:n	Chain of n HTTP 302 redirects (max 20)
/cookies	Inspect request cookies
/cookies/set	Set cookies via query params
/cookies/delete	Delete cookies via query params
/uuid	Random UUID v4
/ip	Client IP address
/user\-agent	User-Agent header echo
/headers	All request headers
/healthz	Health check
/metrics	Request statistics (when enabled)
/endpoints	List all endpoints
/swagger\-ui	OpenAPI documentation
.TE
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is loaded in the following order (later sources override earlier):
.IP 1. 4
Hardcoded defaults
.IP 2. 4
.I /etc/rucho/rucho.conf
(system-wide)
.IP 3. 4
.I ./rucho.conf
(local directory)
.IP 4. 4
Environment variables
.RB ( RUCHO_* )
.PP
.SS Key Parameters
.TS
l l l.
Parameter	Default	Description
_
server_listen_primary	0.0.0.0:8080	Primary HTTP listener
server_listen_secondary	0.0.0.0:9090	Secondary HTTP listener
server_listen_tcp	(none)	TCP echo listener address
server_listen_udp	(none)	UDP echo listener address
ssl_cert	(none)	Path to SSL certificate
ssl_key	(none)	Path to SSL private key
log_level	info	Log level (trace/debug/info/warn/error)
metrics_enabled	false	Enable /metrics endpoint
compression_enabled	false	Enable gzip/brotli compression
http_keep_alive_timeout	75	HTTP idle timeout (seconds)
tcp_keepalive_time	60	TCP keepalive idle time (seconds)
tcp_nodelay	true	Disable Nagle's algorithm
header_read_timeout	30	Max time to read headers (seconds)
chaos_mode	(none)	Chaos types: failure,delay,corruption
.TE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
All configuration parameters can be set via environment variables prefixed with
.BR RUCHO_ .
The variable name is the uppercase form of the parameter name.
For example:
.TP
.B RUCHO_SERVER_LISTEN_PRIMARY
Primary HTTP listen address (default: 0.0.0.0:8080)
.TP
.B RUCHO_LOG_LEVEL
Log level (default: info)
.TP
.B RUCHO_METRICS_ENABLED
Enable the /metrics endpoint (default: false)
.TP
.B RUCHO_COMPRESSION_ENABLED
Enable response compression (default: false)
.TP
.B RUCHO_SSL_CERT
Path to SSL certificate file
.TP
.B RUCHO_SSL_KEY
Path to SSL private key file
.TP
.B RUCHO_CHAOS_MODE
Enable chaos engineering (comma-separated: failure,delay,corruption)
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/rucho
Server binary (when installed via .deb package)
.TP
.I /etc/rucho/rucho.conf
System-wide configuration file
.TP
.I ./rucho.conf
Local configuration file (overrides system-wide)
.TP
.I /var/run/rucho/rucho.pid
PID file for the running server process
.SH EXAMPLES
Start the server with default settings:
.PP
.RS
.nf
rucho start
.fi
.RE
.PP
Test with curl:
.PP
.RS
.nf
curl http://localhost:8080/get
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/post -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"key": "value"}'
curl -i http://localhost:8080/status/503
curl http://localhost:8080/delay/2
.fi
.RE
.PP
Configuration file example (/etc/rucho/rucho.conf):
.PP
.RS
.nf
server_listen_primary = 0.0.0.0:8080
log_level = info
metrics_enabled = true
compression_enabled = true
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run with Docker:
.PP
.RS
.nf
docker run -p 8080:8080 -p 9090:9090 rumpus/rucho:latest
.fi
.RE
